                            <note><locus from="1" to="1">Fol. 1</locus> is a wholly extraneous leaf
                                of much later date. The MS proper begins with <locus from="2" to="2"
                                    >fol. 2.</locus></note>
                            <note>The work seems to be complete down to the 6th bāb of the first
                                faṣl of the 4th maqāla. The remainder is missing, except that <locus
                                    from="30" to="30">fol. 30</locus> contains a fragment of text
                                around the 2nd bāb of the first faṣl of the 5th (and last)
                                maqāla.</note>
