                            <docAuthor/>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Itmām mā fī kitāb al-āla al-shāmila min
                                al-nuqṣān (lil-tihādihā) li-jamīʿ al-buldān</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt"/>
                            <title xml:lang="ara"/>
                            <title xml:lang="ara" type="alt"/>
                            <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc"/>
                            <note>See Yāqūt, Irshād 7,241: '[Badīʻ al-Asṭurlābī] made good a
                                deficiancy in the shāmila instrument which [Khujandi] had invented.
                                The latter had constructed the instrument for one latitude, and
                                proved that it was not possible to make it serve more than one
                                latitude. [Badīʻ al-Asṭurlābī], however, pondered over it and
                                discovered a method of constructing it to serve for various
                                latitudes.' The present text is evidently Badīʻ al-Asṭurlābī's
                                theoretical demonstration of the deficiency of Khujandi's work. </note>
                            <note/>
                            <note/>
